title: Something that still bugs me about post-crisis pre-flashpoint JSA
body: They chased Captain Marvel off when they thought he was a pedophile (they somehow didn’t know he was a teenage and he was starting a relationship with Stargirl and for some reason the wisdom of king baby slicer wouldn’t let him reveal his identity) yet they did nothing when Atom Smasher (an actual grown up adult) got romantically close to her…

summary: CAPTAIN MARVEL #4 KELLY THOMPSON (W) • CARMEN CARNERO (A) Cover by AMANDA CONNER & Paul Mounts ASGARDIAN VARIANT COVER BY FRANK...
caption:
CAPTAIN MARVEL #4

KELLY THOMPSON (W) • CARMEN CARNERO (A)
Cover by AMANDA CONNER & Paul Mounts
ASGARDIAN VARIANT COVER BY FRANK CHO
THE KNOCK-DOWN, DRAG-OUT FIGHT YOU CAN’T MISS!
Nuclear Man reveals his secret weapon: The X-Man ROGUE! It’s been years since Rogue stole Carol’s powers and memories in a fight that changed Carol forever. Though Carol and Rogue have become somewhat uneasy allies in the years since, a wound like that never fully heals. And now, isolated from her allies and facing her worst nightmare, how far will Carol go to stop history from repeating itself?
32 PGS./Rated T+ …$3.99

summary: New ‘Captain Marvel’ footage gives a big nod to ‘Avengers: Infinity War’ post-credits scene
title: New ‘Captain Marvel’ footage gives a big nod to ‘Avengers: Infinity War’ post-credits scene
body:
Marvel just keeps getting better and better!!

Captain Marvel will launch on March 8th, which means we’re going to see an increasing number of TV spots and teasers in the coming weeks, followed by an avalanche of interviews with all the stars in the movie. Just a few days ago I told you that Marvel boss Kevin Feige let it slip that Captain Marvel will lead the Avengers in the future, during a featurette I saw before Glass, but sadly I can’t…

body:
T5W: Top 5 Anticipated Movies of 2019

This week’s Top 5 Wednesday is a freebie topic so I’m using it to talk about the movies I’m most anticipating this year.  Counting down to most anticipated:

5) Toy Story 4

Release Date: June 21

I recently binge-watched the Toy Story trilogy (of course, I was curled up on the floor bawling my eyes out at the end of the third film) so I’m interested to see what happens to Woody and the gang in the…
